Hi Andrew,

For the time being, the best you can do is to test for the existence of the script you're loading on the `window`, and if it exists, don't load it again.

``` javascript
yepnope({
    test : window.jQuery,
    nope: "https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.6.4/jquery.min.js"
});
```

This isn't 100% full proof, because if you're making two yepnope calls to download a script, it may have not executed before the second call has been made, and then won't exist in the `window`.

That being said, we're working on the ability to prevent duplicate script downloads for a future release, so stay tuned.

