The underlying code for jQuery.getScript is the same as in yepnope. The difference is that yepnope executes things in order. If you don't need that functionality, you probably should just use barebones script injection:

``` javascript
(function(d){
  var s = d.createElement('script'),
        t = d.getElementsByTagName('script')[0];
  s.src = 'script.js';
  s.async = true;
  t.parentNode.insertBefore( s, t );
})(document);
```

The fastest it gets, and doesn't make you wait on jQuery.

